item.dc:creator: @usman555 usman555
item.description:
@usman555 wrote:

any java version can compile. You probably have jre instead of jdk. Jdk is java development kit. You can automatically know that it means for making stuff. Define: “development”. Now jre is java runtime environment. That means something else, you don’t gotta know. So download the latest version of jdk which is 20 I believe. and edit your environmental variables and your compiler code.
